comment.body:
****Description:**** Potential SQL Injection detected. Untrusted input is being directly included in an SQL query without proper parameterization. This can allow attackers to modify the query structure and execute arbitrary SQL commands. Use PreparedStatement with parameterized queries instead. Always validate and sanitize inputs before using them in queries. Learn more https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/89.html

****Severity:**** High

review.body:
## Pull Request Overview This is a Snyk-generated security fix PR that addresses 8 vulnerabilities in npm dependencies across multiple example applications. The PR updates package versions to remediate critical security issues including incomplete input validation, prototype pollution, and cross-site scripting vulnerabilities. Key changes: - Updates multiple dependencies across 6 example project package.json files - Addresses vulnerabilities ranging from critical (score 235) to medium severity (score 49) - Primarily focuses on Ember.js example with the most comprehensive dependency updates ### Reviewed Changes Copilot reviewed 51 out of 56 changed files in this pull request and generated no comments.
Show a summary per file | File | Description | | ---- | ----------- | | `examples/ember/package.json` | Major dependency updates including Ember CLI, test helpers, and styling tools to fix multiple vulnerabilities | | `examples/hydrogen/package.json` | Updates PostCSS and Vite to address security issues | | `examples/hydrogen-2/package.json` | Updates Shopify CLI Hydrogen to newer version | | `examples/hexo/package.json` | Updates Hexo from v5.3.0 to v7.2.0 | | `examples/ionic-react/package.json` | Updates React Scripts from 3.3.0 to 5.0.0 | | `package.json` | Updates Vite to patch version 5.1.7 | | `packages/routing-utils/package.json` | Updates Node.js types to newer patch version |

review.body:
## Pull Request Overview This is a Snyk-generated security fix PR that addresses 8 vulnerabilities in npm dependencies across multiple example applications. The PR updates package versions to remediate critical security issues including incomplete input validation, prototype pollution, and cross-site scripting vulnerabilities. Key changes: - Updates multiple dependencies across 6 example project package.json files - Addresses vulnerabilities ranging from critical (score 235) to medium severity (score 49) - Primarily focuses on Ember.js example with the most comprehensive dependency updates ### Reviewed Changes Copilot reviewed 51 out of 56 changed files in this pull request and generated no comments.
Show a summary per file | File | Description | | ---- | ----------- | | `examples/ember/package.json` | Major dependency updates including Ember CLI, test helpers, and styling tools to fix multiple vulnerabilities | | `examples/hydrogen/package.json` | Updates PostCSS and Vite to address security issues | | `examples/hydrogen-2/package.json` | Updates Shopify CLI Hydrogen to newer version | | `examples/hexo/package.json` | Updates Hexo from v5.3.0 to v7.2.0 | | `examples/ionic-react/package.json` | Updates React Scripts from 3.3.0 to 5.0.0 | | `package.json` | Updates Vite to patch version 5.1.7 | | `packages/routing-utils/package.json` | Updates Node.js types to newer patch version |

pull_request.title: feat: add allowValidatorFailure option for graceful validator failures
pull_request.body:
## Summary

- Adds a new `allowValidatorFailure` option to gracefully handle validator failures
- When enabled, returns `undefined` instead of throwing an error when validation fails  
- Provides proper TypeScript type inference for three scenarios:
  - No validator: returns `T | undefined`
  - Validator with `allowValidatorFailure: true`: returns `T | undefined`  
  - Validator with `allowValidatorFailure: false` (default): returns `T`

## Changes

### Core Implementation
- Added `allowValidatorFailure?: boolean` to the `Options<T>` interface
- Modified `LimoFile._read()` method to check the option and return `undefined` instead of throwing
- Updated `ResolvedOptions` type and `resolveOptions` function to handle the new option

### Type Safety  
- Added function overloads for all factory functions (`createLimoText`, `createLimoJson`, `createLimoJsonc`, `createLimoToml`, `createLimoYaml`)
- Overloads provide proper return type inference based on validator configuration
- Maintains backward compatibility with existing code

### Testing
- Added comprehensive tests for validator failure scenarios across all file formats
- Tests cover both `allowValidatorFailure: true` and `allowValidatorFailure: false` cases
- All existing tests continue to pass

## Usage Examples

```typescript
// Returns T | undefined - graceful failure
using json = createLimoJson("file.json", { 
  validator: myValidator, 
  allowValidatorFailure: true 
});
if (json.data === undefined) {
  // Handle validation failure gracefully
}

// Returns T - throws on failure (existing behavior)  
using json = createLimoJson("file.json", { 
  validator: myValidator,
  allowValidatorFailure: false // or omit (default)
});
```

## Test Plan
- [x] All existing tests pass
- [x] New validator failure tests pass for all file formats
- [x] Type checking passes with proper inference
- [x] Linting passes

The following preferences don't have to be set manually anymore:

- `print.show_print_progress`
  - Why: removed
  - Bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1770536
  - Commit: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox/commit/b5226643104eb610ad2b0477a1a5fc6df0aeb65b

- `gfx.offscreencanvas.enabled`
  - Why: removed
  - Bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1914083
  - Commit: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox/commit/7d2c6889202d9fbf6133a30b27bcd07bc06cb107

- `layout.css.round.enabled`
  - Why: removed
  - Bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1874633
  - Commit: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox/commit/97909653e70cdf75b4e3669e178ec7fca6e98110

- `dom.events.asyncClipboard.clipboardItem`
  - Why: enabled by default
  - Bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1887845
  - Commit: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox/commit/de56ae88bf17f74207c40a627be93ccf1bcd2df6

Disable AI/ML features using Firefox preferences for testing

We don't need AI/ML features in the tests, so this should reduce CPU
usage by not having the inference process running. Moreover, it prevents
the following lines from being logged in the test output:

```
JavaScript error: resource://gre/actors/MLEngineParent.sys.mjs, line 509: Error: Unable to get the ML engine from Remote Settings.
JavaScript error: resource://gre/actors/MLEngineParent.sys.mjs, line 1279: TypeError: can't access property "postMessage", this[#port] is null
```

feat: Replace read-only start date with accessible date picker

This commit replaces the read-only start date input with a more accessible and interactive date picker.

Key changes:
- The `startDate` input is now a `type="date"` element, with a fallback to `type="text"` for unsupported browsers.
- Added robust validation to ensure the date is in YYYY-MM-DD format and represents a valid calendar date.
- An inline error message is displayed for invalid input, preventing state updates until the format is correct.
- On valid date changes, the project's start date is updated in the state, and the CPM is recomputed, refreshing all views.
- The help text has been updated to include keyboard navigation hints for better accessibility.

pull_request.title: feat: Replace read-only start date with accessible date picker
pull_request.body:
This commit replaces the read-only start date input with a more accessible and interactive date picker.

Key changes:
- The `startDate` input is now a `type="date"` element, with a fallback to `type="text"` for unsupported browsers.
- Added robust validation to ensure the date is in YYYY-MM-DD format and represents a valid calendar date.
- An inline error message is displayed for invalid input, preventing state updates until the format is correct.
- On valid date changes, the project's start date is updated in the state, and the CPM is recomputed, refreshing all views.
- The help text has been updated to include keyboard navigation hints for better accessibility.
